This blueprint recreates the infrastructure and delivery shell from the bundled PHP reference repository. It is intended for Symfony-oriented services where the application code itself is mounted from `project/`.

## Included

- Docker build files for PHP-FPM and nginx under `build/`
- GitHub composite actions under `.github/actions/`
- A CI/CD workflow under `.github/workflows/pipeline.yml`
- PHP quality tooling via `tools/composer.json`, `phpunit.xml.dist`, and `phpstan.neon.dist`
- Security policy seed material under `sbom/`

## Notes

- Copy `.env.dist` to `.env` and adjust values for your environment.
- Place the actual Symfony application inside `project/`.
- The deployment stages still reference the original external reusable workflows and will usually need adaptation before production use.

